The framework required for running this project on your local machine is as follows:

1. Modules required:
    -Open-cv(cv2)
    -face_recognition
    -numpy
    -os
    -pandas
    -datetime
    -streamlit
    
2. There might be some problem regarding importing of face_recognition library. To solve that problem 
   first we would need to install the dlib wheel on our system. This dlib wheel will vary according to
   python version that is present on our computer. 
   For python versions 3.9:
   Install dlib from the given github repository.
   Link:https://github.com/shashankx86/dlib_compiled
   
   For python version 3.10 use this command in your command prompt:
   pip install https://github.com/jloh02/dlib/releases/download/v19.22/dlib-19.22.99-cp310-cp310-win_amd64.whl
   
   After installing dlib module,install cmake module followed by 
   After that install cmake module.
   
